HEADWORD: margay cat
<hw>margay cat</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small American wild cat
(<spn>Felis wiedi</spn> syn. <spn>Felis tigrina</spn>), ranging from
Mexico to Brazil. It is spotted with black. Called also
<altname>long-tailed cat</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

